body: - https://github.com/twitter/twemoji - a makefile greps all used emoijs from the markup files and downloads the relevant emoij images from github. Cloning the repo would be overkill as it is > 500MB. fixes #14 --- This change is [](https://reviewable.io/reviews/toktok/website/22)

comment_regular_data.body:
Do we need to replicate the emojis in our repo, if we can just download them on page build?

---

Reviewed 9 of 9 files at r1.
Review status: all files reviewed at latest revision, 2 unresolved discussions.

---

*[Makefile, line 25 at r1](https://reviewable.io:443/reviews/toktok/website/22#-Ka24EcynA9UBW9WWir8:-Ka24EcynA9UBW9WWir9:b-chmy8e) ([raw file](https://github.com/toktok/website/blob/bc39b638f82b370f658a3207c8fa7496f070eeab/Makefile#L25)):*
> ```Makefile
> emoij:
> 	mkdir -p toktok/static/img/emoij/16x16
> 	for codepoint in $$(grep -Prhio '&#x[\da-f]+;' toktok/ | grep -ioP '[\da-f]+'); do \
> ```

You can use `make` to parallelise this loop for you.

---

*[Makefile, line 27 at r1](https://reviewable.io:443/reviews/toktok/website/22#-Ka23YJNqHUlwg42wlbE:-Ka23YJNqHUlwg42wlbF:b-1l1f77) ([raw file](https://github.com/toktok/website/blob/bc39b638f82b370f658a3207c8fa7496f070eeab/Makefile#L27)):*
> ```Makefile
> 	for codepoint in $$(grep -Prhio '&#x[\da-f]+;' toktok/ | grep -ioP '[\da-f]+'); do \
> 		echo $$codepoint; \
> 		wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/twitter/twemoji/gh-pages/16x16/$$codepoint.png -O toktok/static/img/emoij/16x16/$${codepoint}.png ; \
> ```

Add `|| exit 1` after the wget command so that it fails when one of the emojis can't be downloaded.

---

commit.message:
use twemoij.js to enable emoij in all browsers

- https://github.com/twitter/twemoji
- a makefile greps all used emoijs from the markup files and
  downloads the relevant emoij images from github. Cloning the repo
  would be overkill as it is > 500MB.
